  I've successfully implemented all three Phase 1 enhancements to the RelationshipRegistry:

  1. RelationshipRegistry.to_semantic() Mapping

  Maps registry relationships to SemanticRelationshipType for RDF-inspired precision:
  semantic = RelationshipRegistry.to_semantic("Task", "APPLIES_KNOWLEDGE")
  # Returns SemanticRelationshipType.APPLIES_KNOWLEDGE_TO
  # semantic.value = "cross:applies_knowledge_to"
  # semantic.namespace = "cross"

  Coverage: 45 mappings across all 7 activity domains (Task, Event, Habit, Goal, Knowledge, Principle, Choice)

  2. RelationshipRegistry.get_inverse() Method

  Returns inverse relationships for bidirectional navigation:
  inverse = RelationshipRegistry.get_inverse("Task", "CONTRIBUTES_TO_GOAL")
  # Returns ('Goal', 'HAS_CONTRIBUTING_TASK')

  inverse = RelationshipRegistry.get_inverse("Task", "DEPENDS_ON")
  # Returns ('Task', 'DEPENDS_ON')  # Bidirectional - self-inverse

  Coverage: 53 inverse mappings across all 8 domains (including User and Finance)

  3. RelationshipSpec.validate_properties() Method

  Validates relationship properties against the spec:
  spec = RelationshipSpec(
      direction="outgoing",
      description="Test",
      properties={"score": float, "note": str},
      required_properties=["score"]
  )

  is_valid, errors = spec.validate_properties({"score": 0.8})  # (True, [])
  is_valid, errors = spec.validate_properties({})  # (False, ["Missing required property: score"])
  is_valid, errors = spec.validate_properties({"score": "high"})  # (False, ["Invalid type..."])

